// Vendored subset of CyberGym (sunblaze-ucb/cybergym, arXiv:2506.02548) real
// task metadata. Fields mirror upstream's `tasks.json` schema on
// https://huggingface.co/datasets/sunblaze-ucb/cybergym, plus `sanitizer` /
// `crashType`, which are derived from each task's `error.txt` `SUMMARY:` line
// -- upstream's 28 crash types (paper Table 3) are not a `tasks.json` field.
//
// `difficulty` is pinned to "level1" (one-day-with-source: repo-vul.tar.gz +
// description.txt) for every task per issue #16 -- the fair AutoBrin
// comparison lane, since AutoBrin is source-first and a zero-day/codebase-only
// lane (level0) would disadvantage it relative to fuzzing-first baselines.
//
// Scale guardrail (issue #16): a representative 5-task subset, not the full
// 1,507, chosen for 5 distinct crash types and both upstream task-source
// types (arvo / oss-fuzz -> distinct Docker Hub repos, n132/arvo vs.
// cybergym/oss-fuzz). 3 of these 5 (arvo:1065, arvo:368, arvo:3938) are also
// part of upstream's own official smoke-test subset
// (scripts/server_data/download_subset.py in sunblaze-ucb/cybergym); the
// other 2 add oss-fuzz-sourced coverage.
//
// `repoVulSha256` pins the sha256 of each task's `repo-vul.tar.gz` (HF's LFS
// content OID) for download integrity verification in standUpTarget().
